<TITLE> Develop cluster communities for rural dev: Muhith </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 12 (bdnews24.com)  Finance minister Abul Maal Abdul Muhith on Tuesday said development of cluster rural communities is essential to ensure rural development and check population influx in urban areas. "We need to develop cluster rural communities It will ensure different services there facilitating sub-contracting jobs and helping industrial sector to develop," he said. The minister was speaking at a seminar on 'Urban poverty: dimension and solution" organised by Power and Participation Research Centre (PPRC) at LGED auditorium in the city. He said begging could be swept away in 4 to 5 years if rural communities are strengthened. Muhith laid emphasis on decentralising public institutions, strengthening local government and increasing facilities to slums dwellers. He pointed out that nowadays only two percent of the national budget is allocated for rural government "though once it was 10 percent of the budget." The minister said services like sanitation and water and power supply should be ensured for slums in the urban area
